<div id="content" class="backgrnd4"><div id="right"><div id="box6"><h2 class="backgrnd12"><span class="text1">The Thirteenth Conference on Innovative Applications of Artificial Intelligence (IAAI-01)</span></h2><div class="content"><p><i>Sponsored by the Association for the Advancement of Artificial Intelligence</i></p><p><b>Edited by Hayam Hirsh and Steve Chien</b></p><p>August 7&ndash;9, 2001, Seattle, Washington. Published by The AAAI Press, Menlo Park, California. <a href="../../Press/Proceedings/iaai01.php">This proceedings is also available in book and CD format.</a></p><p><b>Please Note:</b> Abstracts are linked to individual titles, and will appear in a separate browser window. Full-text versions of the papers are linked to the abstract text. Access to full text may be restricted to AAAI members. PDF file sizes may be large!</p><hr /><h3 class="left">Contents</h3><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/2001/iaai01-000.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">Preface</a> / xix</p><h3 class="left">Deployed Applications</h3><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/2001/iaai01-001.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">CARMA: A Case-Based Range Management Advisor</a> / 3<br />Karl Branting, LiveWire Logic, Inc.; John Hastings, University of Nebraska at Kearney; and Jeffrey Lockwood, University of Wyoming</p><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/2001/iaai01-002.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">TALPS: The T-AVB Automated Load Planning System</a> / 11<br />Paul S. Cerkez, DCS Corporation</p><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/2001/iaai01-003.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">Natural Language Sales Assistant -- A Web-Based Dialog System for Online Sales</a> / 19<br />Joyce Chai, Veronika Horvath, Nicolas Nicolov, Margo Stys-Budzikowska,Nanda Kambhatla, and Wlodek Zadrozny, IBM T. J. Watson Research Center</p><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/2001/iaai01-004.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">Interchanging Agents and Humans in Military Simulation</a> / 27<br />Clinton Heinze, Simon Goss, Torgny Josefsson, Kerry Bennett, Sam Waugh,Ian Lloyd, and Graeme Murray, Department of Defence, Australia;John Oldfield, Royal Australian Air Force</p><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/2001/iaai01-005.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">The RadarSAT-MAMM Automated Mission Planner</a> / 35<br />Benjamin D. Smith, Barbara E. Engelhardt, and Darren H. Mutz, Jet Propulsion Laboratory,California Institute of TechnologyEmerging Applications</p><h3 class="left">Emerging Applications</h3><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/2001/iaai01-006.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">Scaling Up Context-Sensitive Text Correction</a> / 45<br />Andrew J. Carlson, Jeffrey Rosen, and Dan Roth, University of Illinois atUrbana/Champaign</p><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/2001/iaai01-007.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">Electric Elves: Applying Agent Technology to Support Human Organizations</a> / 51<br />Hans Chalupsky, Yolanda Gil, Craig A. Knoblock, Kristina Lerman, Jean Oh, David V. Pynadath, Thomas A. Russ, and Milind Tambe, University of Southern California</p><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/2001/iaai01-008.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">Token Allocation Strategy for Free-Flight Conflict Solving</a> / 59<br />G&eacute;raud Granger, Nicolas Durand, and Jean-Marc Alliot, CENA/LOG, France</p><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/2001/iaai01-009.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">Collaborative Kodama Agents with Automated Learning and Adapting for Personalized Web Searching</a> / 65<br />Tarek Helmy, Satoshi Amamiya, and Makoto Amamiya, Kyushu University, Japan</p><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/2001/iaai01-010.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">Image-Feature Extraction for Protein Crystallization: Integrating Image Analysis and Case-Based Reasoning</a> / 73<br />I. Jurisica and P. Rogers, Ontario Cancer Institute, Canada; J. Glasgow and S. Fortier,Queen&rsquo;s University, Canada; J. Luft, M. Bianca, R. Collins, and G. DeTitta,Haumptman-Woodward Medical Research Institute</p><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/2001/iaai01-011.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">An Open Architecture for Multi-Domain Information Extraction</a> / 81<br />Thierry Poibeau, Thales Research and Technology</p><p class="left"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Library/IAAI/2001/iaai01-012.php" onclick="window.open (this.href, 'child', 'height=500px,width=300px,scrollbars'); return false">Constraint-Based Modeling of InterOperability Problems Using an Object-Oriented Approach</a> / 87<br />Mohammed H. Sqalli and Eugene C. Freuder, University of New Hampshire</p><p class="left">Index / 95</p></div></div></div><div id="left">
